# Portfolio Project Context

Personal portfolio for Aditya Gupta — Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4.

## Directory Layout

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `app/` | Routes, layout, fonts, global CSS, providers |
| `components/navPages/` | Single-page portfolio sections (Home, Experience, Projects, …) |
| `components/ui/` | shadcn-style primitives and effects |
| `lib/` | Shared utilities (`utils.ts`, `blog.ts`, `site.ts`) |
| `content/posts/` | Blog markdown with YAML frontmatter |
| `public/` | Static assets (resume, icons, project images) |

## Routing

- `/` — main portfolio (all sections on one page, hash anchors like `#home`, `#projects`)
- `/blog` — article index; `/blog/[slug]` — individual posts
- `/home` redirects to `/` (see `app/home/page.tsx`)

## Site Config

Centralize URLs and metadata in `@/lib/site`. Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL` in production.

## Commands

After substantive changes: `npm run lint` and `npm run typecheck`. Use `npm run dev:clean` if the dev cache misbehaves.

## Agent Guidelines

- Match existing patterns in neighboring files before adding abstractions
- Keep diffs focused — no drive-by refactors or unrelated changes
- Do not commit `.next/`, `.env`, or generated build artifacts
